{
  "texts": [
    "Emotion, or Face Perception/Recognition (n = publications) Emotion, or Face Perception/Recognition holds publications that focus on the visual behavior associated with viewing different faces or emotion-inducing stimuli to predict the recognized face or the perceived emotion.",
    "These publications explicitly used stimuli depicting different emotions, such as anger and happiness (Lanatà et al., 2013; Kanan et al., 2015; Chaby et al., 2017; Shi et al., 2017), or different people's faces (Coutrot et al., 2016; Chaby et al., 2017; Chuk et al., 2017a; Król and Król, 2019; Necka et al., 2019).",
    "This task group focused explicitly on those types of stimuli, which meant that if a publication focused, for example, on different activities to induce certain emotions, it was not included in this task group.",
    "Reading holds publications that focus on aspects related to reading behavior.",
    "It is built on the assumption that reading could be a unique indication toward understanding a participant's or a text's characteristics."
  ]
}